From COCHRANE JAMES SHAPLEIGH Subject Re Riddle me On the subject of CS CN tear gas when I received my initial introduction to tear gas the first thing that came to mind was the location of the If there had been anything in the way corners to negotiate doors to open or any other obstacles to movement I would have had a difficult time exiting the And any concentration of tear gas is hazardous to individuals with respiratory problems and the wearing of soft contact lenses in a tear gas contaminated area is considered a REAL BAD So hoping the BD's would peaceably come strolling out the door after being gassed is a bit If they could have found the door having them staggering out retching wouldn't be too far Throw in the factor of days of being under siege and subject to psychological warfare and all bets on functional abilities are Anybody tried to get Amnesty International to jump in on this one James Cochrane When in danger or in doubt run in This space circles scream and for rent